kinetic.client

Class AsyncKineticException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • kinetic.client.KineticException
          • kinetic.client.AsyncKineticException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class AsyncKineticException
extends KineticException
    The exception instance that delivers to an asynchronous kinetic request if an error occurred during the asynchronous request.

    When an application calls a KineticClient asynchronous operation, the result is delivered to the registered callback handler. Kinetic client runtime library calls the CallbackHandler.onSuccess(CallbackResult) for each successful asynchronous operation.

    Should an error occurred, such as Version MisMatch for a put() operation, the raised exception is delivered to the registered CallbackHandler. Kinetic client runtime library calls the CallbackHandler.onError(AsyncKineticException) for each failed asynchronous operation.

    Author:
    chiaming
    See Also:
    KineticClient, CallbackHandler, Serialized Form
